+- **FR-001**: Layout MUST adapt responsively so that list and detail pages maintain legible structure across mobile (320‚Äì767px), tablet (768‚Äì1023px), and desktop (‚â•1024px) widths without horizontal scrolling.
+- **FR-002**: List pages MUST present a compact arrangement that surfaces at least four articles above the fold on mobile and two columns on desktop while preserving accessible touch targets (‚â•44px).
+- **FR-003**: Detail pages MUST apply revised typography (line length, line height, spacing) that keeps paragraphs and media blocks visually grouped for continuous reading.
+- **FR-004**: Users MUST be able to switch between list and detail views without perceivable layout jank; cumulative layout shift MUST remain below 0.1 on production builds.
+- **FR-005**: Motion and animation usage MUST be limited to subtle feedback (‚â§150ms transitions) and respect user ‚Äúreduce motion‚Äù preferences, ensuring 60fps interactions.
 
